<p>We recommend <a href="https://www.rodha.co.in" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Rodha</a> as the first platform every CAT aspirant should open, for one checkable reason: it has put its entire teaching (more than 1,400 videos covering the full CAT syllabus, on a channel now past 424,000 subscribers) on YouTube, free. No other brand on this list matches that at this scale. The name is Sanskrit for "bridge," and the backstory explains the philosophy: founder Ravi Prakash came from a middle-class background where coaching fees were a genuine barrier, taught Quant, DI and LR at T.I.M.E. from 2012–16 to learn the industry from inside, personally holds a 99.86 CAT percentile, and then spent a year recording and self-editing 350+ lessons to make the full syllabus free — a journey he describes in this <a href="https://www.eatmy.news/2024/01/ravi-prakash-coming-from-middle-class.html" rel="noopener" target="_blank">founder profile</a>.</p>
