<p>Founded in 1995 by Satya Narayanan R, an IIM Bangalore alumnus who left a corporate job at Ranbaxy to start the company on revenue of roughly ₹96,000 in its first year, a bootstrapped-to-scale story documented in this <a href="https://www.founderthesis.com/p/indias-original-ed-tech-founder-cl" rel="noopener" target="_blank">founder interview</a>, Career Launcher now runs 200+ centres alongside its online programs. It suits students who want the reassurance of a large, long-established organisation with a defined mentor structure.</p>

